ARRAY['All-in-one platform covers billing, cases, and client management', 'Used by 150,000+ legal professionals globally across 90 countries', 'Integrates with 200+ tools including court filing and payment systems', 'Clio Duo AI handles routine drafting and case note summarisation'],
ARRAY['AI features require higher-tier plan beyond the entry level', 'Can feel complex for solo practitioners with simpler practice needs', 'More practice management than deep legal AI research capability'],
ARRAY['Law firm operations, billing, and client matter management', 'AI-assisted client communications and case note summarisation', 'All-in-one practice management for solo and small firm attorneys']),

-- 3. Lexis AI
('lexis-ai', 'Lexis AI', 'AI-powered legal research built into LexisNexis - the world''s largest legal database',
'Lexis AI is LexisNexis''s AI legal research platform, integrating large language model capabilities directly into the world''s largest legal database. For legal professionals who rely on Lexis for case law, statutes, and secondary sources, Lexis AI adds conversational research, brief analysis, and drafting assistance within the platform they already use. The AI retrieves relevant case law from natural language queries, summarises lengthy opinions, and drafts argument sections grounded in cited precedents. Because it draws from LexisNexis''s proprietary database rather than the public web, Lexis AI''s research is more reliable for jurisdiction-specific legal work than general-purpose AI tools. Hallucination risk on legal citations is significantly lower when the AI retrieves from a controlled, authoritative legal database rather than generating citations from training data. Access requires a LexisNexis subscription, with pricing varying significantly by firm size and usage tier. For law firms and legal researchers already on the Lexis platform, the AI features represent a substantial productivity upgrade to existing research workflows without requiring any change in tools.',
