ARRAY['Translates complex legal language into plain English instantly', 'Free tier available for occasional document review without sign-up', 'Highlights clauses that deserve attention before signing', 'Works with any document type including NDAs, leases, and employment contracts'],
ARRAY['Not a replacement for professional legal advice on complex matters', 'Accuracy varies on highly technical or jurisdiction-specific language', 'Free tier limits daily document volume'],
ARRAY['Contract review for freelancers and small business owners', 'Understanding terms of service and privacy policies before signing up', 'Client-facing plain-language summaries of complex legal agreements']),

-- 5. Spellbook AI
('spellbook-ai', 'Spellbook', 'AI contract drafting and review for lawyers - works directly inside Microsoft Word',
'Spellbook is an AI contract drafting and review assistant built for legal professionals, operating as a Microsoft Word add-in that brings AI capabilities directly into the document editing environment lawyers already use daily. Built on GPT-4 and trained on commercial contract data, Spellbook suggests missing clauses, flags unusual provisions, explains legal language in plain terms, and drafts new contract sections from a brief description. Unlike general-purpose AI writing tools, Spellbook understands commercial contract norms and legal drafting conventions, making its clause suggestions appropriate for professional legal work. The Word integration means lawyers can review and draft contracts without switching applications, preserving existing workflows while adding AI assistance. Law firms using Spellbook report 50 to 70 percent reductions in routine contract task time, particularly on first-draft creation and playbook review. Pricing starts at $99 per user per month. Spellbook is primarily used by commercial lawyers and in-house legal teams handling high volumes of contract work who want AI that fits into existing Microsoft Office workflows.',
'https://www.google.com/s2/favicons?domain=spellbook.legal&sz=64',
