ARRAY['Commercial contract review and first-draft acceleration', 'Clause drafting and amendment generation for transactional lawyers', 'In-house legal team contract review at scale across business units']),

-- 6. Zuva
('zuva', 'Zuva', 'AI contract intelligence for bulk document analysis and structured clause extraction',
'Zuva is an AI contract intelligence platform designed for high-volume contract analysis, derived from the technology behind Kira Systems. Zuva reads and extracts structured data from unstructured contract documents, identifying parties, dates, obligations, termination rights, and custom clauses across large contract portfolios. The platform is used by legal teams, corporate development departments, and legal technology firms that need to analyse thousands of contracts during M&A due diligence, lease portfolio reviews, or regulatory audits. Zuva offers a self-serve API for developers integrating contract intelligence into legal workflows, as well as an enterprise platform for non-technical legal teams. The AI models are pre-trained on commercial legal language and can be fine-tuned for specific document types and custom clause definitions. Pricing is enterprise and usage-based, varying by document volume. For organisations managing large contract portfolios under time pressure, Zuva reduces manual review time by 50 to 80 percent on extraction-heavy legal work, with accuracy levels that hold up under legal scrutiny.',
'https://www.google.com/s2/favicons?domain=zuva.ai&sz=64',
