-- 7. ContractBook
('contractbook', 'ContractBook', 'AI-native contract management connecting creation, signing, and obligation tracking',
'ContractBook is a contract management platform that connects creation, signing, and storage in a single workflow with AI-powered data extraction. The platform uses AI to analyse uploaded contracts, populate a structured database of obligations, renewal dates, and counterparties, and send automated reminders for upcoming contract milestones. Unlike basic document storage, ContractBook builds a live contract database that teams can query and act on without manually reading through individual documents. The free tier supports unlimited contracts for up to 3 users, making it accessible for early-stage companies and small teams. Paid plans from $199 per month add workflow automation, advanced reporting, audit trails, and API access for larger operations teams. ContractBook is used by operations teams, finance departments, and in-house legal teams at companies managing 50 to 5,000 active contracts. The platform is particularly well-suited to companies that have outgrown spreadsheet-based contract tracking but do not need the full complexity of enterprise CLM platforms like Ironclad.',
'https://www.google.com/s2/favicons?domain=contractbook.com&sz=64',
