-- 10. Ironclad
('ironclad', 'Ironclad', 'Enterprise contract lifecycle management for legal and business operations teams',
'Ironclad is an enterprise contract lifecycle management (CLM) platform that covers every stage of the contract process from request and drafting through negotiation, execution, and ongoing obligation management. The AI layer assists with clause suggestion, risk flagging, contract summarisation, and automated obligation extraction from executed agreements. Unlike DocuSign or Adobe Sign, which are primarily e-signature platforms with added AI features, Ironclad is built specifically for contract operations teams and designed to replace email chains, shared drives, and spreadsheets as the system of record for all commercial agreements. Legal and business operations teams at enterprise companies use Ironclad to manage vendor agreements, customer contracts, NDAs, and employment agreements in a single platform with full audit trails and approval workflows. Pricing is enterprise and custom. For organisations where contract operations are a significant business function, Ironclad provides the most complete solution from initial contract request through ongoing obligation tracking and renewal management. The platform integrates with Salesforce, Slack, Google Workspace, and major document editing tools.',
